Present location: BIBLIOTHECA ALEXANDRINA ANTIQUETIES MUSEUM [01/027] ALEXANDRIA BAAM
Name: Frieze with Swastikas
Description: A fragment of a limestone frieze, which is decorated with embossed motifs. The decoration consists of two different motifs; on the upper part of the frieze there are four swastikas, in geometrical frames and between them there are three flowers, then there is an embossed line, under which there are four bunches of grapes hanging from branches. The artisan illustrated the details most successfully.
